  document.querySelectorAll('img.lazy').forEach(img => {
    img.loading = 'lazy';
    let imgUrl = img.dataset.src;
    // Only adding width + height for avatars for now

      const targetWidth = img.getAttribute('width') || img.width;
      imgUrl += `?width=${targetWidth}`;
    }
    img.src = imgUrl;
    img.removeAttribute('data-src');
    img.classList.remove('lazy');
    img.classList.add('js-lazy-loaded');
    img.dataset.qa_selector = 'js_lazy_loaded_content';
  });
}

<div class="file-content md">
<h1 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="1:1-1:29">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#millennials-to-snake-people" class="anchor" id="user-content-millennials-to-snake-people"></a>Millennials to Snake People</h1>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="3:1-3:67">Browser extension that reveals the <em>real</em> truth behind Millennials.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="6:1-6:15">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#installation" class="anchor" id="user-content-installation"></a>Installation</h2>
<ol dir="auto" data-sourcepos="8:1-8:48">
<li data-sourcepos="8:1-8:48">Add the extension to your browser of choice:</li>
</ol>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="9:3-14:0">
<li data-sourcepos="9:3-9:114"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/millennials-to-snake-peop/jhkibealmjkbkafogihpeidfcgnigmlf" target="_blank">Chrome</a></li>
<li data-sourcepos="10:3-10:90"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/millennials-to-snake-people/" target="_blank">Firefox</a></li>
<li data-sourcepos="11:3-11:72"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/a2/millennials-to-snake-people/releases" target="_blank">Safari</a></li>
<li data-sourcepos="12:1-14:0"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.google.com/search?q=Millennials" target="_blank">Free your mind</a></li>
</ul>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="15:1-15:7">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#also" class="anchor" id="user-content-also"></a>Also</h2>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="17:1-21:0">
<li data-sourcepos="17:1-17:238">Need headlines automatically converted and tweeted? Follow <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/snakepeople_bot" target="_blank">@snakepeople_bot</a> on Twitter, courtesy of <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/jimkang" target="_blank">jimkang</a>'s <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/jimkang/hail-ants-bot" target="_blank">hail-ants-bot</a>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="18:1-18:295">Uncomfortable that a non-compulsory, intentionally subversive browser extension uses language to affect your worldview, but still want a laugh? Try <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/millennials-to-snake-peop/ekkcdmnckghgcbgkdfbafpgepbmkjhnd?hl=en-US" target="_blank">Millennials to Snake People Pure</a>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="19:1-21:0">Addicted to text replacement plugins? Check out <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/cloud-to-butt-plus/apmlngnhgbnjpajelfkmabhkfapgnoai?hl=en" target="_blank">Cloud to Butt Plus</a>, <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/sjw-to-skeleton/kckodmjikeoncekpplppkkcjolofmacc?hl=en" target="_blank">SJW to Skeleton</a>, <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/millennials-begone/dlgjecnejicmpdknhangcbeahbgipolf?hl=en" target="_blank">Millennials Begone!</a>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="22:1-22:9">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#thanks" class="anchor" id="user-content-thanks"></a>Thanks</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="24:1-24:54">Huge thank you to the following people for their help:</p>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="26:1-41:0">
<li data-sourcepos="26:1-28:62">Ports

</li>

<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="42:1-42:17">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#how-to-disable" class="anchor" id="user-content-how-to-disable"></a>How to disable</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="44:1-44:97">Don't worry! The extension can be re-enabled after <del>it destroys your blog post</del> it is disabled.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="46:1-46:10">

<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="48:1-48:47"><code>Preferences</code> > <code>Extensions</code> > Uncheck <code>Enable</code></p>

<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="54:1-54:10">

    img.loading = 'lazy';
    let imgUrl = img.dataset.src;
    // Only adding width + height for avatars for now
    if (imgUrl.indexOf('/avatar/') > -1 && imgUrl.indexOf('?') === -1) {
      const targetWidth = img.getAttribute('width') || img.width;
      imgUrl += `?width=${targetWidth}`;
    }
    img.src = imgUrl;
    img.removeAttribute('data-src');
    img.classList.remove('lazy');
    img.classList.add('js-lazy-loaded');
    img.dataset.qa_selector = 'js_lazy_loaded_content';
  });
}

    img.loading = 'lazy';
    let imgUrl = img.dataset.src;
    // Only adding width + height for avatars for now
    if (imgUrl.indexOf('/avatar/') > -1 && imgUrl.indexOf('?') === -1) {
      const targetWidth = img.getAttribute('width') || img.width;
      imgUrl += `?width=${targetWidth}`;
    }
    img.src = imgUrl;
    img.removeAttribute('data-src');
    img.classList.remove('lazy');
    img.classList.add('js-lazy-loaded');
    img.dataset.qa_selector = 'js_lazy_loaded_content';
  });
}

</script>

if ('loading' in HTMLImageElement.prototype) {
  document.querySelectorAll('img.lazy').forEach(img => {
    img.loading = 'lazy';
    let imgUrl = img.dataset.src;
    // Only adding width + height for avatars for now
    if (imgUrl.indexOf('/avatar/') > -1 && imgUrl.indexOf('?') === -1) {
      const targetWidth = img.getAttribute('width') || img.width;
      imgUrl += `?width=${targetWidth}`;
    }
    img.src = imgUrl;
    img.removeAttribute('data-src');
    img.classList.remove('lazy');
